snippet.textDisplay:
1. Did you trade mark it?
2. Someone on your team leaked it?
3. Are the materials different?
4. Are the shades the same ?

If you answered no to any of these it leaves it open for others to create similar products. You aren't the first to experience "dupes" (packaging or actual product) by other brands and won't be the last. I'm sure it truly is frustrating as a creator but it's part of the industry.
Unfortunately, for creators, (especially those out of drug store price range) dupes are what many people rely on (particularly the middle or lower classes)- especially if the product quality doesn't compare to lower priced items.
You are allowed your opinion... but it is what is. 🤷🏻‍♀️
